Class Delivery

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.limelight.videosdk.model.Delivery

  • public class Delivery
extends Object
    A Delivery represents a single, playable resource. The most basic element of media is the encoding, but some delivery mechanisms can package multiple encodings into one URL. As such, the delivery represents a collection of one-to-n encodings that are packaged together. As an example, Widevine streaming does automatic bit-rate switching (as does Apple’s HLS), while Widevine offline only has a single bit rate (and, as such, a single encoding).
